        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I can't recall the exact loc on the treasure chests. The one I usually hunted was between the chief camp and the camp towards SG.</P><P>Swim between those two camps until you find a sunken ship. Don't worry about pulling the treasure chest, they have a fairly large aggro range and will attack the moment you get near the ship. Well, ONE will attack. There is only one per sunken ship.</P><P>They don't cast, but they remind me of The Luggage from the Terry Pratchett DiscWorld novels. In other words a treasure chest is a big chest full of teeth. For entertainment, pull one up on the beach and watch how it moves.</P><P>They can be fear kited or root/dotted. They usually drop a gem and always drop 100' of rope for a WW quest.</P><P>You should be able to solo them at 49 I think. They give exp up to 55.</P><P>Umbrax of Rallos Zak<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
