        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I've given away moutain of the boot gems.  Drop a lot in CS.</P><P>Best way to describe the chest is to use the landscape.  It's almost always up as it hits like a truck so people avoid it.</P><P>The camp with the vendors has a big rock next to it.  For easiest pulling, park your pet near it.  Turn to shore.  You will see two cuts in the beach, sharp V-shaped notches.  One might have a otter standing in it.  You want the one second to the left from the rock, or the one next to the otter if he's up.  Put on a shieldskin spell for safety your first pull, DMF, and Jboot (after you are familiar with it you can do without this stuff, but first pull can be rough).  </P><P>Dive in the water, hug the bottom.  You will see a sunken ship.  The chest is hiding inside the bow.  The best and safest way I found to pull is to swim down, make a sharp turn at the boathouse, swim past the bow, turn to shore and run.  If you did this right, the chest will be chasing you.  Press F9 four times to get a few behind you.  </P><P>If you weren't hit, run out of the water about 20 feet and stop.  Target chest, send pet.  Snare, fear, dot if you want to/need to.  Med.  Chest will make a big circle around the camp and die on the far side.  Fear pathing is lovely =)  Chest can drop any of the velious gems, or a bottle of beer and 1 cp.  It's a lottery ticket.</P><P><i><b><font color=gold><font size=4>Dinomight Questaholic</b></font id=size4><BR>Master of the Lizard Dance on Test  {The Grove}</i></font id=gold><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

